A newly established Chinese charity group has offered Sh1million to a community school in Mukuru slums. The funds will be used in the acquisition of new textbooks for the new curriculum and desks for St. Stephens Integrated schools. The school has a population of over 1,000 students in itsÂ primary and secondary level. The Chuanyu association is a chamber of commerce founded by Guangqi Xie bringing together Chinese entrepreneurs from two provinces; Chongqing and Sichuan. Their businesses in Kenya vary from real estate, hospitality, casinos, construction and general products imports. Speaking at the event, CS Raphael Tuju praised the formation of the new association saying that with the growing strong economic bond between Kenya and China, it will come in handy straightening any differences that may arise and also promote more business. Click here for the latest political news